# Speedwell Project Conventions

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 with App Router
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4
- clsx for conditional class names
- Swiper.js for sliders
- Headless UI for modals/dialogs
- Iconify for icons
- Luxon for date/time handling

## Block Components

### File Structure

- All block components go in `src/blocks/`
- Name files as `{block-name}.tsx` (lowercase, hyphenated)
- Hero blocks use sequential numbering: `hero-1.tsx`, `hero-2.tsx`, etc.
- Check existing hero files to find the next available number

### Naming Conventions

- Export function name should be PascalCase matching the file name
- `hero-16.tsx` → `export default function Hero16()`
- `business-info.tsx` → `export default function BusinessInfo()`

### Component Guidelines

- Use `'use client'` directive only when needed (hooks, interactivity, event handlers)
- Import shared components from `@/components`
- Do not copy imports/components from other projects - adapt to this project's conventions

## Styling

### Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind classes exclusively, not inline styles (inline styles break hover effects)
- Use `clsx` for conditional classes:

  ```tsx
  import clsx from 'clsx'

  className={clsx(
    'base-classes',
    index === 0 && 'bg-body/0',
    index === 1 && 'bg-body/2',
    index === 2 && 'bg-body/4'
  )}
  ```

### Color Tokens

- Text: `text-body`, `text-contrast`, `text-accent`, `text-accent-contrast`
- Background: `bg-body`, `bg-contrast`, `bg-accent`, `bg-accent2`, `bg-accent3`, etc.
- Accent colors have contrast variants: `bg-accent` pairs with `text-accent-contrast`

### Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Common pattern: `flex-col xl:flex-row`

## Imports

### Path Aliases

- Use `@/` path alias for src directory
- Components: `import { Heading, Paragraph, Icon } from '@/components'`
- Hooks: `import useCircleAnimation from '@/hooks/use-circle-animation'`
- Blocks: `import BusinessInfo from '@/blocks/business-info'`

### Icons

- Use Iconify packages: `@iconify/icons-heroicons/`, `@iconify/icons-carbon/`, etc.
- Import specific icons: `import playIcon from '@iconify/icons-heroicons/play-solid'`
- Render with Icon component: `<Icon icon={playIcon} className="w-6 h-6" />`

## Available Components

### Typography

- `Heading` - with props: `as`, `color`, `className`, `textAlign`, `margin`
- `Paragraph` - with props: `variant` ("large"), `color`, `className`, `textAlign`, `margin`
- `Accent` - with props: `size`, `color`, `margin`, `textAlign`

### Interactive

- `Button` - with props: `href`, `variant` ("primary", "outline")
- `Buttons` - wrapper for button groups
- `VideoPopup` - modal video player with Vimeo support
- `Icon` - Iconify icon wrapper

### Layout

- `Cover` - background image/video sections
- `Container` - max-width wrapper
- `Section` - semantic section wrapper

## Hooks

### Location

- All hooks go in `src/hooks/`
- Name files as `use-{hook-name}.tsx`
- Include a markdown documentation file: `use-{hook-name}.md`

### Available Hooks

- `useCircleAnimation` - animates rotating text circles on scroll
- `SwiperSliderInit` - initializes Swiper sliders with props: `swiperId`, `autoHeight`

## Creating New Blocks

1. Check `src/blocks/` for the highest numbered file of that type
2. Create new file with incremented number
3. Use PascalCase function name matching file name
4. Import components from `@/components`
5. Hardcode all content
6. Use Tailwind for all styling

## Do NOT

- Use `classnames` package - use `clsx` instead (it's installed)
- Import components/utilities from other projects without adapting them
- Create documentation files unless explicitly requested
